description: A rocket has hit a sports complex filled with children playing soccer in the Israeli-controlled Golan Heights region Saturday afternoon, on the same day that an Israeli strike in Gaza devastated a school building and killed dozens.
title: A rocket hit Israeli-controlled Golan Heights, after Israel struck a Gaza school

description: Coach Bev Priestman and two former members of Canada's coaching staff cannot work in soccer for a year. In addition, the Canadian women's team received a penalty that likely ends its Olympic hopes.
title: FIFA suspends Canada's women's soccer coach for one year after Olympic spying scandal

description: Gamblers have wagered hundreds of millions of dollars on who Vice President Kamala Harris will choose as her running mate.
title: Gamblers bet millions on Kamala Harris's VP pick

description: Former House Speaker Nancy Pelosi has had a historic career. Even after she stepped aside from party leadership, her influence remains strong.
title: A year after her speakership ending, Nancy Pelosi’s influence remains strong

description: When a Texas resident found an abandoned baby owl at a family barbecue, she acted fast to rescue it -- using a warm tortilla.
title: How an abandoned baby owl was rescued in a warm tortilla

description: An Israeli airstrike hit yet another school sheltering displaced people in Gaza. Later, a rocket strike in the Israeli-controlled Golan Heights hit a soccer field where kids were playing.
title: Children were main casualties in strikes in Gaza and near Israel's Northern border

description: With the opening ceremony wrapped up, the competition at the Paris Olympics really gets underway. On Saturday, among the notable events are some swimming finals and men's gymnastics preliminaries.
title: After opening ceremony, Paris Olympics are really getting started

description: A attack on a soccer field in the Israeli-controlled Golan Heights wounded several other people hours after an Israeli airstrike on south Lebanon killed three members of Hezbollah.
title: Rocket attack on Israeli-controlled Golan Heights kills 10, rescue official says

description: The school, where thousands were sheltering, was being used by displaced Palestinians and the deaths included several children. Israel's military said it was targeting a Hamas command center.
title: At least 30 dead in Gaza after an Israeli airstrike hits a school used as a shelter

description: How do you cool down without air conditioning? Our readers respond with clever hacks involving towels, ice packs — anc pickle.
title: We asked, you answered: How do you stay cool without air conditioning?

description: Divers Sarah Bacon and Kassidy Cook won the first U.S. medal of the Paris Olympics: a silver in the 3-meter synchronized springboard. It's the first time the U.S. has medaled in the event since 2012.
title: Team USA wins its first medal of the Paris Summer Olympics

description: Two astronauts have been hanging out on the International Space Station since last month, waiting for the Boeing capsule that got them there to be repaired to bring them home.
title: Opinion: Think you have a rough travel story? Try 52 days stuck in space

description: On military bases from Virginia to the Middle East, pistols made by New Hampshire-based Sig Sauer have allegedly fired without a trigger pull, seriously wounding soldiers in some instances.
title: Sig Sauer guns hanging on soldiers’ hips may be firing without trigger pull

description: Simone Biles is the most decorated gymnast in history. But she withdrew from the last summer Olympic Games due to mental health struggles. Her journey is chronicled in the new Netflix series Simone Biles Rising.
title: Simone Biles reminds us: You never know what Olympic athletes are going through

description: The women's 400-meter freestyle will feature the three women who have collectively held a lock on the world record for the ten years and counting: Katie Ledecky, Ariarne Titmus and Summer McIntosh.
title: The Olympics open with a titanic showdown in the pool: The women's 400m freestyle

description: As hazy air from fires out West wafts across the country, some people are at higher risk of health problems, including children, older people and those with lung conditions. Here's how to stay safe.
title: Here's who is most at risk from wildfire smoke and how to protect yourself

description: California's largest active fire exploded in size on Friday evening, growing rapidly amid bone-dry fuel and threatening thousands of homes as firefighters scrambled to meet the danger.
title: California's largest wildfire explodes in size as fires rage across US West

description: The US Justice Department late Friday accused TikTok of harnessing the capability to gather bulk information on users based on views on divisive social issues like gun control, abortion and religion.
title: Justice Dept. claims TikTok collected views on issues like abortion and gun control

description: Images from the opening ceremony of the 2024 Olympic Games offer a stunning glimpse into the dramatic and heavily Parisian-themed day.
title: First look: Photos from Paris Olympics opening ceremony
